node.title: Tairāwhiti records two new community cases - the region's first this year
node.description: The positive results follow repeated positive wastewater test results in the Tairāwhiti area this month.
node.content: ["Two Covid-19 cases have been reported in Tair\u0101whiti today.", "Both people are in the same household - the second person has been in self-isolation and will remain there for another 9 days.", "There are no places of interest at this point.", "The positive results follow repeated wastewater tests detecting Covid-19 in the Tair\u0101whiti area this month.", "People are urged to get tested if they have symptoms.", "There's a testing centre on Peel Street in Gisborne which is open today, Chirstmas Day and Boxing Day.", "Just yesterday, locals told RNZ they were concerned about Covid-19 reaching their region, but said it was inevitable it would.", "The last case was last year - a person who had been in managed isolation and did not infect anyone else.", "Ninety percent of eligible people in the region have had their first dose of the vaccine.", "RNZ"]
